1 B. As used in this section, “deed theft” means to:
2 1. Intentionally alter, falsify, forge, or misrepresent
3 property documents such as a residential or commercial deed or
4 title, with the intent to deceive, defraud, or unlawfully transfer
5 or encumber the ownership rights of a residential or commercial
6 property;
7 2. Misrepresent oneself as the owner or authorized
8 representative of residential or commercial real property in order
9 to obtain ownership or possession of such real property; or
10 3. With intent to defraud take, obtain, steal, or transfer
11 title or ownership of real property by fraud, forgery, larceny, or
12 any other fraudulent or deceptive practice.
